Next Steps Updated: In our last remote session we discussed that In effort to reduce the repetitive logs (300 million) under file tracing we recommended to customer to exclude .uasset file extensions from file tracing, customer will also decide on other file extensions to exclude from file tracing after internal discussions with their team.  Customer will let us know after they have decided which other file extensions to exclude from file tracing.  After we have received an update from customer, we will assist them if required on how to configure audit log backups.  To reduce the size of their live database "/var/eppfiles/mysql" they will need to run the audit log backup making sure to uncheck "Keep backed up logs" and "Keep backed up shadows".

What We've Learned Updated: Due to repetitive logs (300 million) under file tracing .uasset file extensions the customer database have grown very big in size +120 SQL database. We recommended to customer to exclude .uasset file extensions from file tracing to reduce the number of entries of event logs under file tracing.
